Naradisoft Privacy Policy

At Naradisoft, we are committed to protecting your privacy and personal information. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and share information when you use our website and mobile applications (the "Services").

Information We Collect

We collect information from you when you use our Services, including:

Personal information, such as your name, email address, and phone number, which you may provide when you create an account or contact us for support.

Device information, such as your IP address, device type, and operating system, which is collected automatically when you use our Services.

Location information, such as your device's GPS coordinates, which may be collected if you have enabled location services on your device.

Usage information, such as the pages you visit and the features you use within our Services, which is collected automatically through the use of cookies and similar technologies.

Payment information, such as your credit card or bank account details, which may be collected if you make a purchase through our Services.

How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect to provide and improve our Services, and to communicate with you. Specifically, we may use your information for the following purposes:

To create and manage your account.

To provide customer support and handle technical issues.

To send you marketing and promotional communications, if you have opted in to receive them.

To analyze and understand how our Services are used, and to improve and optimize our Services.

To process and fulfill orders and transactions.

To comply with legal and regulatory requirements.

Sharing Your Information

We may share your information with third parties in the following circumstances:

With service providers and partners who perform services on our behalf, such as payment processors and hosting companies.

With law enforcement or other government agencies, as required by law or in response to a valid request.

In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or part of our business.

Your Choices and Rights

You have the following choices and rights with respect to your personal information:

You can opt out of receiving marketing communications from us by following the unsubscribe instructions in the emails you receive, or by contacting us at [contact email].

You can request access to, or correction of, your personal information by contacting us at [contact email].

You can request that we delete your personal information by contacting us at [contact email].

Please note that certain information may be required in order for us to provide our Services, and that we may need to retain certain information for legal or compliance purposes.

Children's Privacy

Our Services are not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under the age of 13, we will take steps to delete such information.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes to our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will post any changes on this page and encourage you to review our privacy policy regularly.

Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about our privacy practices, please contact us at [contact email].
